Time: Approx 2pm - 4pm<br>
What: Kill steal of the Wraith of Shissar<br>
Where: Plane of Fear<br>
Who: A bunch of At Death's Door asswipes.<br>
<br>
Basically what happened is this:<br>
We noticed the Wraith of Shissar was up in Fear earlier in the day, and this being Maeve's very last epic piece, we decided to gather the force to go kill it.<br>
<br>
About 2pm we perform our run in, drag bodies, res up, and begin pulling about 3pm. After about an hour of pulling roamers and clearing portal so friends to come in to help with the temple pull, At Death's Door enters the zone riding on our coattails. I had been sent tells previously by Banelion telling me that they were going to attempt to engage the Wraith <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> even though they knew we had been there clearing for that express purpose.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Seeing that things were heating up, we kicked the raid into overdrive, pulling out the entire temple so that we could pull the Wraith. Bippity snags the Wraith and begins nuking/snaring/aggro'ing her and bringing her into camp. Verbo from ADD then enages the Wraith <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> while it is being pulled by us</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and brings it to his group where they kill it and Qindien loots the epic piece that should have been Maeve's.<br>
<br>
Then they have the audicity to blame <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> me</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for the train their puller brings into their camp. But thats really beside the point and just goes to show what d*ckheads these people are.<br>
<br>
The GM-Admin has been informed, and I sincerely hope he brings justice to the situation, though I'm guessing we'll just have to do this all again.<br>
<br>
Recap: Radiant enters and clears roamers/temple in Fear, pulls Wraith. ADD takes pull and KSes.<br>
<br>
Kasik I'm sorry you were a part of this, and thank you for your words. As for the rest of ADD, this isn't our first issue with you, nor will I bet it will be the last. Radiant takes care of its own and its members interact with other players with dignity and respect.<br>
<br>
We have long memories. Don't expect any respect from us.<br>
<br>
Tristadorn Champion of Scale<br>
Guildleader<br>
